{"_path":"/articles/git-hooks","_dir":"articles","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"Git hooks with 2.54.0","description":"Git hooks can be setup in local config files","date":"2026-05-10T00:00:00.000Z","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Since Git 2.54.0, you can now setup your hooks in local git config. This allows to easily configure and share hooks with your team, without a third party helper to setup. In this article, I share how I set it up and how I replace Husky with it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"how-to-setup"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How to setup"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-git","code":"[hook \"lint-commit\"]\n  event = pre-commit\n  command = yarn commitlint \\${1}\n","language":"git","meta":"","style":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"[hook \"lint-commit\"]\n  event = pre-commit\n  command = yarn commitlint \\${1}\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"First, create a "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".gitconfig"}]},{"type":"text","value":" in your repository. Add the config of your choice. Then, tell git where your config is:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-sh shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark","code":"git config set --local include.path ../.gitconfig\n","language":"sh","meta":"","style":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":1},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#B392F0"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"git"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" config"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" set"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" --local"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" include.path"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" ../.gitconfig\n"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The path is relative to your "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".git/config"}]},{"type":"text","value":" file. Running this command edits it to add:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-git","code":"[include]\n    path = ../.gitconfig\n","language":"git","meta":"","style":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"[include]\n    path = ../.gitconfig\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"how-to-remove-husky"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How to remove Husky"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Husky was a great tool to share hooks until now. Now, it's not needed anymore. Here are the steps to remove:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ol","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"remove reference from your local git config"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"remove the dependency from package.json"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"replace husky setup command with git's"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here are the commands to run:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{"className":"language-sh shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark","code":"# This should return your local husky folder. In my case, it was `.husky`\ngit config --local core.hooksPath\n# To remove it\ngit config --local --unset core.hooksPath\n\nyarn remove husky\n","language":"sh","meta":"","style":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":1},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#6A737D"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"# This should return your local husky folder. In my case, it was `.husky`\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":2},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#B392F0"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"git"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" config"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" --local"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" core.hooksPath\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":3},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#6A737D"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"# To remove it\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":4},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#B392F0"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"git"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" config"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" --local"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" --unset"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" core.hooksPath\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":5},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"emptyLinePlaceholder":true},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":6},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#B392F0"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"yarn"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" remove"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"style":"--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":" husky\n"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In my package.json, I used to have "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"yarn run postinstall"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to run husky. Now I replaced it with "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"git config set --local include.path ../.gitconfig"}]},{"type":"text","value":". New contributor can allow benefits from the hooks."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"style","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"html.dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark);background: var(--shiki-dark-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-dark-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-dar